<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Edinburgh, Scotland</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Edinburgh Whisky is a family-owned business that specializes in maturing and bottling single malt whisky. The website's refined color palette and sophisticated imagery effectively advertise the company's premium and high-quality offerings, while the simple-to-navigate page layouts ensure a great user experience.</p><p>The website's high-resolution images effectively capture the natural beauty and elegance of the business' location, while the smooth browsing experience allows readers to easily explore the product's diverse flavors and expressions, read more about the company's origins, and shop their product range.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website's tartan-inspired background ties in with the company's Scottish heritage and adds an interesting design element to all pages. The "Our Social" section encourages increased user engagement. WAVE picked up only a few contrast errors throughout the site, indicating optimal readability.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>While the shopping process is intuitive, the site would benefit from additional sections, such as blog posts and client testimonials, to enhance the company's online presence. Additional CTA buttons toward the top of the website would be beneficial for optimal navigation.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-edinburgh-whisky-3840x9448-20240610_2024-06-11-101842_fpze.webp"
